01:59:46.770 --> 01:59:48.470
nor do not banish reasonfor inequality;

2591
01:59:48.470 --> 01:59:50.030
but let your reason serve

2592
01:59:50.030 --> 01:59:52.800
To make the truth appearwhere it seems hid,

2593
01:59:52.800 --> 01:59:55.800
And hide the false seemstrue.

2594
01:59:55.800 --> 01:59:57.430
Many that are not mad

2595
01:59:57.430 --> 01:59:59.070
Have, sure, more lack ofreason.

2596
01:59:59.070 --> 02:00:02.930
What would you say?

2597
02:00:02.930 --> 02:00:05.670
I am the sister of oneClaudio,

2598
02:00:05.670 --> 02:00:07.700
Condemn'd upon the act offornication

2599
02:00:07.700 --> 02:00:10.770
To lose his head;condemn'd by Angelo:

2600
02:00:10.770 --> 02:00:12.200
I, in probation of asisterhood,

2601
02:00:12.200 --> 02:00:14.300
Was sent to by my brother;one Lucio

2602
02:00:14.300 --> 02:00:15.770
As then the messenger

2603
02:00:15.770 --> 02:00:18.400
That's I, an't like yourgrace:

2604
02:00:18.400 --> 02:00:20.370
I came to her fromClaudio, and desired her

2605
02:00:20.370 --> 02:00:23.100
To try her graciousfortune with Lord Angelo

2606
02:00:23.100 --> 02:00:24.900
For her poor brother'spardon.

2607
02:00:24.900 --> 02:00:25.900
That's he indeed.

2608
02:00:25.900 --> 02:00:27.000
You were not bid to speak.

2609
02:00:27.000 --> 02:00:27.870
No, my good lord;

2610
02:00:27.870 --> 02:00:29.770
Nor wish'd to hold mypeace.

2611
02:00:29.770 --> 02:00:30.930
I pray you now, then;

2612
02:00:30.930 --> 02:00:32.200
Pray you, take note of it:

2613
02:00:32.200 --> 02:00:33.870
and when you have abusiness for yourself,

2614
02:00:33.870 --> 02:00:35.270
pray heaven you then beperfect.

2615
02:00:35.270 --> 02:00:36.870
I warrant your honour.

2616
02:00:36.870 --> 02:00:38.700
The warrants for yourself;take heed to't.

2617
02:00:40.830 --> 02:00:42.770
This gentleman toldsomewhat of my tale

2618
02:00:42.770 --> 02:00:43.670
Right.

2619
02:00:43.670 --> 02:00:45.300
It may be right; but youare i' the wrong

2620
02:00:45.300 --> 02:00:49.030
To speak before your time.Proceed.

2621
02:00:49.030 --> 02:00:51.370
I went to this perniciouscaitiff deputy

2622
02:00:51.370 --> 02:00:53.270
That's somewhat madlyspoken.

2623
02:00:53.270 --> 02:00:53.970
Pardon it;

2624
02:00:53.970 --> 02:00:55.430
The phrase is to thematter.

2625
02:00:55.430 --> 02:00:57.900
Mended again. The matter;proceed.

2626
02:00:57.900 --> 02:01:00.970
In brief, to set theneedless process by,

2627
02:01:00.970 --> 02:01:03.630
How I persuaded, how Ipray'd, and kneel'd,

2628
02:01:03.630 --> 02:01:05.370
How he refell'd me, andhow I replied,--

2629
02:01:05.370 --> 02:01:07.400
For this was of muchlength,

2630
02:01:07.400 --> 02:01:08.330
--the vile conclusion

2631
02:01:08.330 --> 02:01:12.300
I now begin with grief andshame to utter:

2632
02:01:13.870 --> 02:01:16.700
He would not, but by giftof my chaste body

2633
02:01:16.700 --> 02:01:18.800
To his concupiscibleintemperate lust,

2634
02:01:18.800 --> 02:01:21.830
Release my brother; and,after much debatement,

2635
02:01:21.830 --> 02:01:24.200
My sisterly remorseconfutes mine honour,

2636
02:01:24.200 --> 02:01:27.500
And I did yield to him:but the next morn betimes,

2637
02:01:27.500 --> 02:01:30.330
His purpose surfeiting, hesends a warrant

2638
02:01:30.330 --> 02:01:31.970
For my poor brother'shead.

2639
02:01:31.970 --> 02:01:33.430
This is most likely!

2640
02:01:33.430 --> 02:01:35.930
O, that it were as like asit is true!

2641
02:01:35.930 --> 02:01:36.900
By heaven, fond wretch,

2642
02:01:36.900 --> 02:01:39.470
thou knowist not what thouspeak'st,

2643
02:01:39.470 --> 02:01:41.700
Or else thou art suborn'din hateful practise

2644
02:01:41.700 --> 02:01:43.570
against his honour.

2645
02:01:43.570 --> 02:01:48.030
First, his integritystands without question.

2646
02:01:48.030 --> 02:01:49.200
Next, it imports no reason

2647
02:01:49.200 --> 02:01:50.830
That with such vehemencyhe should pursue

2648
02:01:50.830 --> 02:01:53.030
Faults proper to himself:

2649
02:01:53.030 --> 02:01:54.830
if he had so offended,

2650
02:01:54.830 --> 02:01:56.700
He would have weigh'd thybrother by himself

2651
02:01:56.700 --> 02:01:59.330
And not have cut him off.

2652
02:01:59.330 --> 02:02:02.100
Some one hath set you on:

2653
02:02:02.100 --> 02:02:04.530
Confess the truth, and sayby whose advice

2654
02:02:04.530 --> 02:02:08.130
Thou camest here tocomplain.

2655
02:02:08.130 --> 02:02:11.630
And is this all?

2656
02:02:11.630 --> 02:02:13.300
Then, O you blessedministers above,

2657
02:02:13.300 --> 02:02:15.770
Keep me in patience, andwith ripen'd time

2658
02:02:15.770 --> 02:02:17.770
Unfold the evil which ishere wrapt up

2659
02:02:17.770 --> 02:02:23.570
In countenance! Heavenshield your grace from woe,

2660
02:02:23.570 --> 02:02:26.400
As I, thus wrong'd, henceunbelieved go!

2661
02:02:26.400 --> 02:02:28.100
I know you'ld fain begone.

2662
02:02:28.100 --> 02:02:29.870
An officer! To prison withher!

2663
02:02:29.870 --> 02:02:30.700
Shall we thus permit

2664
02:02:30.700 --> 02:02:32.070
A blasting and ascandalous breath

2665
02:02:32.070 --> 02:02:34.170
to fall on him so near us?

2666
02:02:34.170 --> 02:02:36.530
This needs must be apractise.

2667
02:02:36.530 --> 02:02:38.300
Who knew of Your intentand coming hither?

2668
02:02:38.300 --> 02:02:41.870
One that I would werehere, Friar Lodowick.

2669
02:02:41.870 --> 02:02:43.730
A ghostly father, belike.

2670
02:02:43.730 --> 02:02:45.130
Who knows that Lodowick?

2671
02:02:45.130 --> 02:02:48.770
My lord, I know him; 'tisa meddling friar;

2672
02:02:48.770 --> 02:02:50.170
I do not like the man:

2673
02:02:50.170 --> 02:02:51.330
had he been lay, my lord

2674
02:02:51.330 --> 02:02:53.130
For certain words he spakeagainst your grace

2675
02:02:53.130 --> 02:02:55.670
In your retirement, I hadswinged him soundly.

2676
02:02:55.670 --> 02:02:59.870
Words against me?a good friar, belike!

2677
02:02:59.870 --> 02:03:01.570
And to set on thiswretched woman here

2678
02:03:01.570 --> 02:03:04.830
Against our substitute!Let this friar be found.

2679
02:03:04.830 --> 02:03:06.500
My lord. but yesternight,she and that friar,

2680
02:03:06.500 --> 02:03:08.600
I saw them at the prison:

2681
02:03:08.600 --> 02:03:11.670
a saucy friar, a veryscurvy fellow.

2682
02:03:11.670 --> 02:03:13.670
Blessed be your royalgrace!

2683
02:03:13.670 --> 02:03:15.270
I have stood by, my lord,

2684
02:03:15.270 --> 02:03:17.500
and I have heard yourroyal ear abused.

2685
02:03:17.500 --> 02:03:18.600
First, hath this woman

2686
02:03:18.600 --> 02:03:20.370
Most wrongfully accusedyour substitute,

2687
02:03:20.370 --> 02:03:22.770
Who is as free from touchor soil with her

2688
02:03:22.770 --> 02:03:24.670
As she from one ungot.

2689
02:03:24.670 --> 02:03:27.330
We did believe no less.

2690
02:03:27.330 --> 02:03:28.900
Know you that Friar Lodowickthat she speaks of?

2691
02:03:28.900 --> 02:03:31.730
I know him for a mandivine and holy;

2692
02:03:31.730 --> 02:03:34.100
Not scurvy, nor atemporary meddler,

2693
02:03:34.100 --> 02:03:36.170
As he's reported by thisgentleman;

2694
02:03:36.170 --> 02:03:38.430
And, on my trust, a manthat never yet

2695
02:03:38.430 --> 02:03:41.000
Did, as he vouches,misreport your grace.

2696
02:03:41.000 --> 02:03:43.300
My lord, most villanously;believe it.

2697
02:03:43.300 --> 02:03:45.400
Well, he in time may cometo clear himself;

2698
02:03:45.400 --> 02:03:47.370
But at this instant he issick my lord,

2699
02:03:47.370 --> 02:03:51.270
Of a strange fever. Uponhis mere request,

2700
02:03:51.270 --> 02:03:52.430
Being come to knowledgethat there was complaint

2701
02:03:52.430 --> 02:03:54.830
Intended 'gainst LordAngelo, came I hither,

2702
02:03:54.830 --> 02:03:57.370
To speak, as from hismouth, what he doth know

2703
02:03:57.370 --> 02:03:59.270
Is true and false;

2704
02:03:59.270 --> 02:04:00.370
and what he with his oath

2705
02:04:00.370 --> 02:04:02.730
And all probation willmake up full clear,

2706
02:04:02.730 --> 02:04:05.670
Whensoever he's convented.First, for this woman.

2707
02:04:05.670 --> 02:04:07.800
To justify this worthynobleman,

2708
02:04:07.800 --> 02:04:10.630
So vulgarly and personallyaccused,

2709
02:04:10.630 --> 02:04:13.800
Her shall you heardisproved to her eyes,

2710
02:04:13.800 --> 02:04:16.130
Till she herself confessit.

2711
02:04:16.130 --> 02:04:19.230
Good friar, let's hear it.

2712
02:04:19.230 --> 02:04:24.330
Do you not smile at this,Lord Angelo?

2713
02:04:24.330 --> 02:04:26.500
O heaven, the vanity ofwretched fools!

2714
02:04:26.500 --> 02:04:28.370
Give us some seats. Come,cousin Angelo;

2715
02:04:28.370 --> 02:04:29.930
In this I'll be impartial;

2716
02:04:29.930 --> 02:04:34.670
you be judge of your owncause.

2717
02:04:38.100 --> 02:04:41.600
Is this the witness,friar?

2718
02:04:47.730 --> 02:04:49.700
First, let her show herface, and after speak.

2719
02:04:49.700 --> 02:04:51.900
Pardon, my lord; I willnot show my face

2720
02:04:51.900 --> 02:04:54.470
Until my husband bid me.

2721
02:04:54.470 --> 02:04:55.670
What, are you married?

2722
02:04:55.670 --> 02:04:56.900
No, my lord.

2723
02:04:56.900 --> 02:04:58.030
Are you a maid?

2724
02:04:58.030 --> 02:04:58.730
No, my lord.

2725
02:04:58.730 --> 02:04:59.970
A widow, then?

2726
02:04:59.970 --> 02:05:01.370
Neither, my lord.

2727
02:05:01.370 --> 02:05:02.200
Why, you are nothing then:

2728
02:05:02.200 --> 02:05:04.570
neither maid, widow, norwife?

2729
02:05:04.570 --> 02:05:07.800
My lord, she may be apunk;

2730
02:05:07.800 --> 02:05:08.900
for many of them

2731
02:05:08.900 --> 02:05:12.070
are neither maid, widow,nor wife.

2732
02:05:12.070 --> 02:05:13.130
Silence that fellow:

2733
02:05:13.130 --> 02:05:14.400
I would he had some cause

2734
02:05:14.400 --> 02:05:15.500
To prattle for himself.

2735
02:05:15.500 --> 02:05:16.770
Well, my lord.

2736
02:05:16.770 --> 02:05:20.100
My lord; I do confess Ine'er was married;

2737
02:05:20.100 --> 02:05:23.070
And I confess besides I amno maid:

2738
02:05:23.070 --> 02:05:25.470
I have known my husband;yet my husband

2739
02:05:25.470 --> 02:05:28.830
Knows not that ever heknew me.

2740
02:05:29.100 --> 02:05:31.600
He was drunk then, mylord:

2741
02:05:31.600 --> 02:05:33.000
it can be no better.

2742
02:05:33.000 --> 02:05:35.430
For the benefit ofsilence,

2743
02:05:35.430 --> 02:05:37.600
would thou wert so too!

2744
02:05:37.600 --> 02:05:38.730
Well, my lord.

2745
02:05:38.730 --> 02:05:40.030
This is no witness forLord Angelo.

2746
02:05:40.030 --> 02:05:42.400
Now I come to't my lord

2747
02:05:42.400 --> 02:05:44.600
She that accuses him offornication,

2748
02:05:44.600 --> 02:05:48.170
In self-same manner dothaccuse my husband,

2749
02:05:48.170 --> 02:05:49.500
And charges him my lord,

2750
02:05:49.500 --> 02:05:50.870
with such a time

2751
02:05:50.870 --> 02:05:53.330
When I'll depose I had himin mine arms

2752
02:05:53.330 --> 02:05:56.530
With all the effect oflove.

2753
02:05:56.530 --> 02:05:58.170
Charges she more than me?

2754
02:05:58.170 --> 02:06:00.130
Not that I know.

2755
02:06:00.130 --> 02:06:01.330
No? you say your husband.

2756
02:06:01.330 --> 02:06:05.470
Why, just, my lord, andthat is Angelo,

2757
02:06:05.470 --> 02:06:08.300
Who thinks he knows thathe ne'er knew my body,

2758
02:06:08.300 --> 02:06:14.300
But knows he thinks thathe knows Isabel's.

2759
02:06:14.300 --> 02:06:18.500
This is a strange abuse.Let's see thy face.

2760
02:06:18.500 --> 02:06:23.970
My husband bids me; now Iwill unmask.

2761
02:06:24.830 --> 02:06:28.500
This is that face, thoucruel Angelo,

2762
02:06:28.500 --> 02:06:31.870
Which once thou sworestwas worth the looking on;

2763
02:06:31.870 --> 02:06:33.930
This is the hand which,with a vow'd contract,

2764
02:06:33.930 --> 02:06:36.700
Was fast belock'd inthine;

2765
02:06:36.700 --> 02:06:37.800
this is the body

2766
02:06:37.800 --> 02:06:40.470
That took away the matchfrom Isabel,

2767
02:06:40.470 --> 02:06:42.170
And did supply thee at thygarden-house

2768
02:06:42.170 --> 02:06:45.430
In her imagined person.

2769
02:06:45.430 --> 02:06:47.270
Know you this woman?

2770
02:06:47.270 --> 02:06:49.030
Carnally, she says.

2771
02:06:49.030 --> 02:06:50.470
Sirrah, no more!

2772
02:06:50.470 --> 02:06:52.270
Enough, my lord.

2773
02:06:52.270 --> 02:06:55.970
My lord, I must confess Iknow this woman:

2774
02:06:55.970 --> 02:06:57.230
And five years since therewas

2775
02:06:57.230 --> 02:06:58.670
some speech of marriage

2776
02:06:58.670 --> 02:07:01.300
Betwixt myself and her;which was broke off,

2777
02:07:01.300 --> 02:07:02.600
Partly for that herpromised proportions

2778
02:07:02.600 --> 02:07:04.270
Came short of composition,but in chief

2779
02:07:04.270 --> 02:07:09.070
For that her reputationwas disvalued

2780
02:07:09.070 --> 02:07:12.900
In levity: since whichtime of five years

2781
02:07:12.900 --> 02:07:14.730
I never spake with her,saw her,

2782
02:07:14.730 --> 02:07:15.500
nor heard from her,

2783
02:07:15.500 --> 02:07:16.800
Upon my faith and honour.

2784
02:07:16.800 --> 02:07:18.470
Noble prince,

2785
02:07:18.470 --> 02:07:20.370
As there comes light fromheaven

2786
02:07:20.370 --> 02:07:22.170
and words from breath,

2787
02:07:22.170 --> 02:07:26.170
As there is sense in truthand truth in virtue,

2788
02:07:26.170 --> 02:07:28.670
I am affianced this man'swife as strongly

2789
02:07:28.670 --> 02:07:31.670
As words could make upvows:

2790
02:07:31.670 --> 02:07:33.370
and, my good lord,

2791
02:07:33.370 --> 02:07:37.030
But Tuesday night lastgone in's garden-house

2792
02:07:37.030 --> 02:07:39.730
He knew me as a wife.

2793
02:07:39.730 --> 02:07:40.730
As this is true,

2794
02:07:40.730 --> 02:07:43.670
Let me in safety raise mefrom my knees

2795
02:07:43.670 --> 02:07:46.330
Or else for ever beconfixed here,

2796
02:07:46.330 --> 02:07:49.770
A marble monument!

2797
02:07:49.770 --> 02:07:53.170
I did but smile till now:

2798
02:07:53.170 --> 02:07:57.700
Now, good my lord, give methe scope of justice

2799
02:07:57.700 --> 02:07:59.870
My patience here istouch'd.

2800
02:07:59.870 --> 02:08:00.830
I do perceive

2801
02:08:00.830 --> 02:08:02.270
These poor informal womenare no more

2802
02:08:02.270 --> 02:08:03.900
But instruments of somemore mightier member

2803
02:08:03.900 --> 02:08:06.470
That sets them on: let mehave way, my lord,

2804
02:08:06.470 --> 02:08:08.030
To find this practise out.

2805
02:08:08.030 --> 02:08:09.970
Ay, with my heart

2806
02:08:09.970 --> 02:08:12.300
And punish them to yourheight of pleasure.

2807
02:08:12.300 --> 02:08:14.200
Thou foolish friar,

2808
02:08:14.200 --> 02:08:15.600
and thou pernicious woman,

2809
02:08:15.600 --> 02:08:17.600
Compact with her that'sgone,

2810
02:08:17.600 --> 02:08:19.270
think'st thou thy oaths,

2811
02:08:19.270 --> 02:08:21.870
Though they would sweardown each particular saint,

2812
02:08:21.870 --> 02:08:24.070
Were testimonies againsthis worth and credit

2813
02:08:24.070 --> 02:08:28.000
That's seal'd in approbation?You, Lord Escalus,

2814
02:08:28.000 --> 02:08:30.070
Sit with my cousin; lendhim your kind pains

2815
02:08:30.070 --> 02:08:33.730
To find out this abuse,whence 'tis derived.

2816
02:08:33.730 --> 02:08:34.970
There is another friarthat set them on;

2817
02:08:34.970 --> 02:08:36.030
Let him be sent for.

2818
02:08:36.030 --> 02:08:37.730
Would he were here, mylord! for he indeed

2819
02:08:37.730 --> 02:08:39.230
Hath set the women on tothis complaint:

2820
02:08:39.230 --> 02:08:42.200
Your provost knows theplace where he abides

2821
02:08:42.200 --> 02:08:43.900
And he may fetch him.

2822
02:08:43.900 --> 02:08:45.400
Go do it instantly.

2823
02:08:45.400 --> 02:08:47.030
And you, my noble andwell-warranted cousin,

2824
02:08:47.030 --> 02:08:49.300
Whom it concerns to hearthis matter forth,

2825
02:08:49.300 --> 02:08:51.400
Do with your injuries asseems you best,

2826
02:08:51.400 --> 02:08:54.270
In any chastisement: I fora while will leave you;

2827
02:08:54.270 --> 02:08:57.730
But stir not you till youhave well determined

2828
02:08:57.730 --> 02:09:00.470
Upon these slanderers.

2829
02:09:00.470 --> 02:09:03.200
My lord, we'll do itthroughly.

2830
02:09:03.730 --> 02:09:12.430
(applause)

2831
02:09:12.430 --> 02:09:15.600
Signior Lucio, did not yousay you knew that

2832
02:09:15.600 --> 02:09:18.170
Friar Lodowick to be adishonest person?

2833
02:09:18.170 --> 02:09:21.370
'Cucullus non facitmonachum:'

2834
02:09:21.370 --> 02:09:23.900
honest in nothing but inhis clothes;

2835
02:09:23.900 --> 02:09:24.870
and one that hath spoke

2836
02:09:24.870 --> 02:09:26.900
most villanous speeches ofthe duke.

2837
02:09:26.900 --> 02:09:28.470
We shall entreat you toabide here

2838
02:09:28.470 --> 02:09:31.930
till he come and enforcethem against him:

2839
02:09:31.930 --> 02:09:33.770
we shall find this friar anotable fellow.

2840
02:09:33.770 --> 02:09:36.270
As any in Vienna, on myword.

2841
02:09:36.270 --> 02:09:38.130
Call that same Isabel hereonce again;

2842
02:09:38.130 --> 02:09:40.500
I would speak with her.

2843
02:09:40.500 --> 02:09:44.430
Pray you, my lord, give meleave to question;

2844
02:09:44.430 --> 02:09:45.870
you shall see how I'llhandle her.

2845
02:09:45.870 --> 02:09:48.130
Not better than he, by herown report.

2846
02:09:48.130 --> 02:09:49.300
Say you?

2847
02:09:49.300 --> 02:09:51.770
